============= Iteration statements ==================

--------------- What is the for loop -----------------
Any Loop you have to define
1-initial value for the counter
2-condition
3-Applying block of codes
4-increment counter


What is the syntax for this loop:
In Java, the for loop is used to execute a block of code a specific number of times.
It has a concise syntax that includes initialization, condition, and increment/decrement steps all in one line.
Here is the general syntax for a for loop:

for (initialization; condition; update or counter ) {
    // Code to be executed
}
Explanation of the Syntax:
Initialization: This part is executed once when the loop starts.
It typically initializes a loop control variable.
Condition: This is evaluated before each iteration.
If the condition is true, the loop body is executed. If it is false, the loop terminates.
Update: This is executed after each iteration of the loop body.
It usually increments or decrements the loop control variable.
---------------------------------------- SHAPES OF TYPING FOR LOOP ----------------------

int i=1;
for(;i<=10;i++)
print()

----------------
int i=1;
for (;i<=10;){
print
i++;
}
----------------
int i;
for(i=0;i++<10;)
print()
----------------
int i;
for(i=0;++i<10;)
print()
-----------
int i=0;
for(;;){
if(i<10)
{ //block of codes uaAmer }
i++;
}

  int count = 0;

        for (;;) {
            System.out.println("Count: " + count);
            count++;

            // Break the loop when count reaches 10
            if (count == 10) {
                break;
            }
        }

        System.out.println("Loop terminated.");


